`TUTORIAL ---------------- IPCS - Address Operands --------------------
`Command ===>_ZCMD
`
`                             address <:address>
~
~An`address operand~may be either a single address or an address range.
~An address may be a symbolic address, a relative address, a literal add
~general-purpose register, a floating-point register, or an indirect add
~An address expression may also be used.
~
~A`symbolic address~is a symbol consisting of 1-31 characters. The first
~character must be an alphabetic or national character ($, @, #). The sa
~characters plus the decimal digits (0-9) may be used for any of the rem
~characters.
~
~A`relative address~is 1-8 hexadecimal digits preceded by a plus sign (+
~
~A`literal address~is 1-8 hexadecimal digits. If the initial digit is a
~(A-F), the literal address must end with a period.
~
~A`general-purpose register~is designated as a decimal integer (0-15) fo
~by an R.
~                               (continued)
